4. Lazy loading module routing
https://angular.io/guide/lazy-loading-ngmodules
ng g m feature/a-lazy-module --route a-lazy-module -m app

5. Content projection
https://angular.io/guide/content-projection
ng-content

6. Angular service
https://angular.io/tutorial/toh-pt4
ng g s services/global-service
When you provide the service at the root level, Angular creates a single,
shared instance of service and injects into any class that asks for it.
Registering the provider in the @Injectable metadata also allows Angular to optimize an application by removing the service
if it turns out not to be used after all.

-- root service is shared by all lazy load modules

